{
  "texts": [
    "Flan-Alpaca and Vicuna 13B perform similarly good.",
    "T5 also shows how much of an effect finetuning has, since the base model scores only 13.6% which means 24% to 30% increase absolute.",
    "One notable exception is mT0 xP3 XXL, which is a multi-lingual version of T5.",
    "It seems that its subpar performance with only 20.9% correct answers is due to the multi-lingual pretraining since BloomZ 7B is also finetuned with xP3 and shows very good results.Vicuna and Flan-Alpaca tend to give correct, but longer answers on average (93 and 115 characters) compared to the T5 models (~16 characters) and also compared to LLaMA, GLM and BloomZ (between 50 and 15 characters).",
    "They are more similar to ChatGPT in this respect (128 characters).WizardLM [51] performs very well in 4 bit GPTQ version with 13b parameters from TheBloke (53.6%) and therefore clearly outperforms Flan T5."
  ]
}